RT  Yersiniabactin synthetase: a four-protein assembly line producing the
RT  nonribosomal peptide/polyketide hybrid siderophore of Yersinia pestis.
RA  Miller DA, Luo L, Hillson N, Keating TA, Walsh CT;
RL  Chem Biol. 2002;9:333-344.
RN  [2]
RM  16751485
RT  Yersiniabactin production by Pseudomonas syringae and Escherichia coli,
RT  and description of a second yersiniabactin locus evolutionary group.
RA  Bultreys A, Gheysen I, de Hoffmann E;
RL  Appl Environ Microbiol. 2006;72:3814-3825.
CC  Yersiniabactin is a siderophore found in a number of enterobacteria,
CC  including Yersinia pestis and some strains of Escherichia coli. Its
CC  biosynthesis and utilization may coexist in an organism with other
CC  siderophore systems such as enterobactin and aerobactin. Yersiniabactin
CC  is made from salicylate, three cysteines, and a malonyl group by a
CC  nonribosomal peptide synthetase/polyketide synthase.
